rule.logic:
ALL of the following must be observed within a 3-minute sliding window:
(1) rclone.exe process spawn where parent process name NOT in ['svchost.exe', 'lsass.exe', 'services.exe', 'wininit.exe', 'explorer.exe'] AND parent process integrity level ≠ 'System';
(2) Sysmon Event ID 10 with TargetImage ending in '\lsass.exe' AND Operation='ProcessAccess' AND GrantedAccess includes '0x1010' (PROCESS_QUERY_INFORMATION | PROCESS_VM_READ);
(3) ≥3 distinct outbound TLS handshakes (detected via firewall or network sensor) to 198.51.100.23:443, with SNI field matching 'malicious-updates.example' OR empty SNI + JA3 hash matching known Cobalt Strike profile;
(4) DNS query for 'malicious-updates.example' from same source host (db-prod-01) within ±60s;
(5) Asset context confirms db-prod-01 is *directly exposed* to a vulnerable PAN-OS firewall (evidence: 'exposed_to_panos:true' tag AND 'panos_version' attribute < '10.2.5-h3' OR 'panos_cve_2024_3400_status:affected').
